  "text": "Similarly, v is the earliest arrival time at the node v. An upper time bound, v , is provided on a terminal node. At each terminal node, v, the latest arrival time e v can be at most equal to v . diff is the maximum difference between the longest and the shortest delay to any node from the inputs. diff is the component of the clock period which can be controlled by buffer insertion. The problem (3) is to be solved subject to the given values of diff and v . All the variables involved here, including w uYv , uYv , v , and diff , are real, thus realizing a Linear Programming [CITATION_1] problem. The problem (3) can be restricted to our IP formulation (1) under the following conditions:",
